Take note that in this formula, the values that will be obtained are the equity and the debt. In order to get the debt-equity ratio, we will simply divide the value of the debt by the value of the equity:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Debt-equity ratio}&=\dfrac{\text{Debt}}{\text{Equity}}
\end{aligned}$$

To get the value of the debt and the equity, we will first assign a variable. For this, we will let $D$ be the debt. From this, we can also then get the equity which is basically the total cost minus the debt.

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Equity}&=\$37,200,000 -\text{D}
\end{aligned}$$
